# Todoist

Access Todoist via the **Auth** project MCP server.

## Tasks

- All work must have a Todoist task (parent module or subtask).
- When starting work, use or create the task that tracks that scope.
- Subtasks hold implementation detail; parent tasks stay high level.

## Comments

- Add comments on the **active working task** as you go — decisions, blockers, what shipped, context for the next agent or for me.
- After each commit tied to a task, comment on that task with a **link to the commit** (SHA or remote URL).

## Planning

When I ask to plan, follow `AGENTS.md` workflow: pick the open task, investigate, present a plan, add subtasks after alignment.

## Module completion

- Do not start the next **parent/module** task until I explicitly say to move on.
- At module end, add review subtasks and wait for my whole-module review.
